#: .\items\books.json
msgid "schematics for APEX Mk I suit"
msgid_plural "schematics for APEX Mk I suits"
msgstr[0] "APEX Mk I 套装设计图"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'schematics for APEX Mk I suit'}
#: .\items\books.json
msgid ""
"Detailed set of instructions for manually turning prototype Mk 0 suit into a"
" Mk I. Requires digitizing the suit by inserting and insulating the "
"governing AI module and the cables connected to holder bracers placed at "
"joint locations. An alternative is suggested in using a molecular forge to "
"speed up the process considerably, with instructions supplied for the "
"process as well."
msgstr ""
"一套详细的手动将原型Mk 0套装升级为Mk "
"I的说明。需要通过插入并绝缘主导AI模块以及连接到关节处固定支架的电缆来实现套装的数字化。建议使用分子锻造机来显著加快此过程，并附有相关操作说明。"

#: .\items\books.json
msgid "schematics for APEX Mk I suit (processing)"
msgid_plural "schematics for APEX Mk I suit (processing)s"
msgstr[0] "APEX Mk I 套装设计图（处理中）"

#. ~ Use action msg for {'str': 'schematics for APEX Mk I suit (processing)'}.
#: .\items\books.json
msgid "schematics turn usable"
msgstr "设计图已可用"

#. ~ Use action not_ready_msg for {'str': 'schematics for APEX Mk I suit
#. (processing)'}.
#: .\items\books.json
msgid "schematics not yet ready"
msgstr "设计图尚未就绪"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'schematics for APEX Mk I suit (processing)'}
#: .\items\books.json
msgid ""
"Data on producing APEX Mk I suit, currently compiling. It could be used in "
"crafting once fully rendered."
msgstr "关于制造APEX Mk I套装的数据，目前正在编译中。一旦完全渲染完成，即可用于制作。"

#: .\items\books.json
msgid "Bitter Logic tangents (APEX Mk I suit)"
msgid_plural "Bitter Logic tangents (APEX Mk I suit)s"
msgstr[0] "苦涩逻辑切线（APEX Mk I 套装）"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'Bitter Logic tangents (APEX Mk I suit)'}
#: .\items\books.json
msgid ""
"A set of tangents - logical premises - for the EULER design asssitance "
"system. This one is labeled \"suit, Mk I\". The only other human-language "
"text on all pages is the hastily-scribbled \"how to turn prototype into real"
" thing\"."
msgstr ""
"一套针对EULER设计辅助系统的切线——逻辑前提。这份标记为“套装，Mk I”。所有页面上唯一其他的人类语言文本是匆忙涂写的“如何将原型变成真品”。"

